  "description": "Autonomous software testing platform using deterministic simulation",
  "long_description": "Antithesis is a commercial autonomous testing platform that uses deterministic simulation to find bugs in distributed systems. Founded by FoundationDB engineers, it runs software in a fully deterministic simulator where all inputs (network, disk, time, randomness) are controlled. This enables perfect reproducibility of failures and systematic exploration of the state space. Used by MongoDB, Palantir, and other companies testing critical infrastructure.",

